822
00:55:39,320 --> 00:55:43,233
I want to be happy. Don't you?

823
00:55:43,400 --> 00:55:45,755
What is happiness anyway?

824
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:49,073
I don't know.

825
00:55:49,240 --> 00:55:51,231
You tell me, you wrote the book.

826
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:53,516
I guess I don't know.

827
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:09,679
- Patrick...
- It was nice being married to you.

828
00:56:10,720 --> 00:56:12,312
You, too.

829
00:56:14,760 --> 00:56:17,991
- Thanks.
- Goodbye, Emma.

830
00:56:24,520 --> 00:56:28,115
Oh! Oh, oh!

831
00:57:13,720 --> 00:57:17,190
I'm sorry I'm late.
I know, I'm always so prompt.

832
00:57:17,360 --> 00:57:21,911
Don't worry. When I arrived, I told them
to bring the drinks in ten minutes.

833
00:57:22,080 --> 00:57:25,072
- How's that for timing?
- Oh, what a day. You have no idea.

834
00:57:25,240 --> 00:57:28,038
Actually, I kind of do.

835
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:29,997
I heard your show today.

836
00:57:30,160 --> 00:57:32,230
- That was Sullivan, I take it?
- Yes.

837
00:57:32,400 --> 00:57:35,153
The good news is I got the papers.

838
00:57:35,320 --> 00:57:39,472
Everything but page 127,
and I'm sure it's in there somewhere.

839
00:57:39,640 --> 00:57:43,349
- We'll never see him again.
- So why don't you look happy?

840
00:57:43,520 --> 00:57:45,112
I am.

841
00:57:47,120 --> 00:57:49,714
Well, I've got something
that might cheer you up.

