886
01:00:46,360 --> 01:00:49,432
So, what if I'm, uh,
losing my footing in my department.

887
01:00:49,600 --> 01:00:53,070
...and I'm asking for a second opinion?

888
01:00:53,240 --> 01:00:57,119
Well, I think Richard is a...

889
01:00:57,280 --> 01:00:59,111
...a good, safe bet. You know?

890
01:00:59,280 --> 01:01:02,158
He's the kind of guy
that you've always gravitated toward.

891
01:01:02,320 --> 01:01:06,393
...and advised other women to pursue,
isn't he?

892
01:01:06,560 --> 01:01:10,678
Probably the type of fellow that my
brand of fatherhood pushed you into.

893
01:01:10,840 --> 01:01:13,035
Look, honey, I mean...

